It builds and packages third-party software, each under its own license.

fetch-sources.sh downloads two unmodified upstream OpenGrm releases:

- OpenGrm BaumWelch - Apache-2.0 - https://www.opengrm.org/
- OpenGrm NGram - Apache-2.0 - https://www.opengrm.org/

kalpy_090/fix-lattice-return.patch is a one-line backport of a change from kalpy-kaldi 0.10.1 to 0.9.0. kalpy is licensed under the MIT License. https://github.com/mmcauliffe/kalpy

The patches under patches/ modify conda-forge feedstock recipes, which are BSD-3-Clause.

The resulting Docker image additionally installs, from conda-forge and Ubuntu:

- Montreal Forced Aligner - MIT - https://github.com/MontrealCorpusTools/Montreal-Forced-Aligner
- Kaldi - Apache-2.0
- OpenFst - Apache-2.0
- Pynini - Apache-2.0
- SoX - GPL-2.0 and LGPL-2.1

Each retains its own license within the image.

